                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-227-victim1930 t18301209-227-viclabel1272"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18301209-227-crimeloc1273">New-street, Covent-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-227-crimeloc1273" type="placeName" value="New-street, Covent-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-227-crimeloc1273" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-227-off1270 t18301209-227-crimeloc1273"></join>. I had a hat in my window for sale on the 8th of December, about nine o'clock in the evening; I had seen it about half-past eight - about nine o'clock I heard a noise in the window, and heard something fall inside the shop; on hearing that, I looked and missed the hat - I looked out and saw the prisoner about twenty yards from the door, carrying the hat in his hand before him; he turned his head round, saw me, and ran away -I followed him, and he dropped the hat; he was stopped before I lost sight of him - this is the hat, it is worth five shillings.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going home - this gentleman called Stop thief! and took me.</p>
               <p>
            
